      "date": "2016-07-09 06:50:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn general I also prefer not to have \"-r\" when deleting only files. That reduces the danger of mistakes if e.g. tfile=\"foo \" then it tries to run:\n\n rm -rf $DIR/foo *\n\nwhich might be bad, or if DIR=\"\" and tfile=\"\" then it becomes:\n\n rm -rf /*\n\nwhich is much worse.\n\nThat said, the current patch is already much better in this regard than the older code, so I'm reluctant to block this from landing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
